Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 11 April 2025

At Data Retrieval Space ("we", "our", or "us"), we are committed to protecting the privacy of individuals who use our data collection services. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, share, and protect your information when you interact with our services, particularly through WhatsApp and automated tools like n8n.

1. Information We Collect
We collect the following types of personal and financial data:

User Information: WhatsApp display name

Receipt Details: Vendor name, description of goods and services, tax base, GST amount, and other financial information contained in submitted receipts or tax invoices

Metadata: Submission timestamps and delivery logs (via WhatsApp or other platforms)

2. How We Collect Data
Your data is collected when you submit images of receipts or invoices through WhatsApp. We use automated tools including n8n to extract relevant financial data using Optical Character Recognition (OCR) and other workflow automation services. Other applications may be integrated as necessary to support this process.

3. Why We Collect Your Data
We collect and process your information in order to:

Facilitate the preparation of expense reports for reimbursement

Support Finance and Accounts Payable (AP) workflow processes

Improve operational efficiency and service accuracy

4. Data Sharing
We do not sell or share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes.
Your data is shared only with the Finance department of the company that you are employed under, for reimbursement and accounting purposes.

5. User Rights and Choices
Access and Usage: You may access and use our services via WhatsApp.

Opt-Out: You may opt out of using our services at any time by ceasing to submit data.

Data Retention: Submitted data will be retained in accordance with our internal deletion cycle policies. We do not offer immediate deletion upon request.

6. Cookies and Tracking
At this time, cookies and tracking tools may be used if you access any associated web-based services. If so, additional disclosures will be provided at the point of interaction.

7. Security
We use appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure. However, no method of data transmission or storage is 100% secure.

8. Children’s Privacy
Our services are not intended for individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect data from children.

9. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates will be reflected by the “Effective Date” at the top of this page. Continued use of the service after changes constitutes acceptance of the new policy.

10. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact:
Email: thomastay@tak.com.sg
